<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America and Merrill Lynch&#39;s Global Corporate and Investment Banking Asia Pacific business executes a client-led Corporate Banking strategy that has resulted in a highly profitable platform with sustainable revenue streams in excess of US$1 billion.  The group serves as a trusted advisor to premier corporate, institutional and government clients, helping them develop their strategic objectives and meet their financial needs by providing advice, financing, and services to a wide range of clients worldwide.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Placement</H3>
<p class="bac">
Associates are hired and placed directly with a specific group.  Group placement is determined by considering business needs and the interests/skills of the Associate.  The groups span across country, industry and product (not all groups exist in all countries):
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Country
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Hong Kong</li>
			<li>Japan</li>
			<li>Singapore</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Industry
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Consumer and Retail</li>
			<li>Energy and Power</li>
			<li>Financial Institutions</li>
			<li>Healthcare</li>
			<li>Industrials</li>
			<li>Real Estate</li> 
			<li>Resources</li>
			<li>Telecom, Media and Technology</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Product
		<ul class="bac">
			<li>Financial Sponsors</li>
			<li>General Execution</li>
			<li>Mergers and Acquisitions</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>

<br>
<H3 class="bac">Responsibilities</H3>
<p class="bac">
Investment Banking Associates play a key role in the origination and execution of work with key clients and take on many responsibilities, including but not limited to:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Working on deal teams with senior bankers and experts from other areas within the firm </li>
	<li>Conducting sophisticated financial analysis and relevant industry research </li>
	<li>Participating in due diligence sessions </li>
	<li>Assisting with structuring transactions, pricing and distributing securities, and closing deals </li>
	<li>Be involved in developing new businesses, preparing and participating in client presentations, and marketing new products</li>
	<li>Assessing the impact of a transaction on a client&#39;s financial results and capital structure</li>
</ul>

